            "prereq_text": "Prerequisites: <a href=\"https://mcgill.ca/study/2019-2020/courses/ecse-509\" target=\"_blank\">ECSE 509</a> and <a href=\"https://mcgill.ca/study/2019-2020/courses/ecse-500\" target=\"_blank\">ECSE 500</a>",
            "coreq_text": "",
            "restrict_text": "",
            "title": "ECSE 506 Stochastic Control & Decision Theory (3 credits)",
            "overview": "Electrical Engineering : Modelling of stochastic control systems, controlled Markov processes, dynamic programming, imperfect and delayed observations, linear quadratic and Gaussian (LQG) systems, team theory, information structures, static and dynamic teams, dynamic programming for teams,multi-armed bandits.",
