            "restrict_text": "",
            "title": "MATH 541 Nonlife Actuarial Models (4 credits)",
            "overview": "Mathematics &amp; Statistics (Sci) : Stochastic models and inference for loss severity and claim frequency distributions; computational techniques for the aggregation of independent risks (Panjer's algorithm, FFT, etc.); risk measures and quantitative risk management applications; models and inference for multivariate data, heavy-tail distributions, and extremes; dynamic risk models based on stochastic processes and ruin theory.",
