            "title": "MATH 566 Advanced Complex Analysis (4 credits)",
            "overview": "Mathematics &amp; Statistics (Sci) : Simple connectivity, use of logarithms; argument, conservation of domain and maximum principles; analytic continuation, monodromy theorem; conformal mapping; normal families, Riemann mapping theorem; harmonic functions, Dirichlet problem; introduction to functions of several complex variables.",
